entry.title: U.S. Postal Service's Search For Savings Brings Riskier Drivers
entry.content: The agency’s new strategy of using freight brokers to cut its rates for long-haul trucking raises questions about highway safety.

entry.title: Ukraine's Offensive Meets Strong Russian Riposte
entry.content: Fierce battles have ensued in the south and east of the country as Russian forces push back against Kyiv’s counteroffensive, a top Ukrainian official said.

entry.title: Migrants' Perilous Route to Europe Is at Its Busiest---and Deadliest---in Years
entry.content: The number of people taking the perilous voyage across the Mediterranean Sea to Europe has surged to a six-year high.

entry.title: When AI Overrules the Nurses Caring for You
entry.content: Artificial intelligence raises difficult questions about who makes the call in a health crisis: the human or the machine?
